               <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                  <tr>
                     <td width="100%" align="left" class="TableCellHeading">An Earthdawn Terminology</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="100%" class="TableCellHeading">
                        <p align="right"><i>By James Flowers,
                              16 June 2004</i></p>
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="100%" align="left" class="TableCell">One of the new additions to the Compendiums is a Glossary of terms referenced in the Earthdawn rules. At present, this is
                        being worked on and added to as we work through the rules: adding an entry here, trying to provide a concise description for
                        that term, and cross-referencing as we go.
                        
                        <p>A thought struck me this evening as I added descriptions for another half-dozen terms. "Why not open this part of the project
                           up to the Earthdawn community?" While I see the Glossary as a useful (and essential) addition to the comprehensive tomes we
                           are working on, it also has value as a supplement in its own right; and likely for both editions of the Earthdawn game as
                           well.
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>So my line of thinking is, when I get back from holiday in a few weeks time, I might just PDF the current "Glossary in Progress"
                           and post it up to the EDC site so that you, as fans, can add your piece to the new rulebooks. Thoughts and comments welcomed
                           on this idea, either replying to this blog posting, or on the Product Development Forum.
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>There is a caveat: while we won't be giving away free stuff to those who help with this, and there won't be a financial payment,
                           we will make a point of acknowledging you in the printed book credits.
                        </p>
                        
                        <p>Back to it again. More spell descriptions beckon...</p>
                        
                        <p>Take kaer, J;)</p>
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <td width="100%" align="right" class="TableCellSmall"><a href="/blogs/checkShow.html">Back to blog</a></td>
